🧠 Build AI Apps with ChatGPT, DALL·E, and GPT-4 – MOOC Summary
This repository contains project code, notes, and resources from the “Build AI Apps with ChatGPT, DALL·E, and GPT-4” course. The course focuses on using OpenAI’s generative models to create intelligent, interactive applications with real-world impact.

📘 Course Overview:
This hands-on course explores how to build AI-powered applications using:

ChatGPT (GPT-4) for natural language understanding and generation

DALL·E for AI-driven image generation from text prompts

Practical integration of OpenAI APIs with Python or JavaScript

Application logic and UI/UX for AI products

Prompt engineering and user interaction flows

🛠️ Skills & Technologies:
Generative AI (ChatGPT & DALL·E)

API Integration (OpenAI Platform)

AI App Development (Frontend & Backend)

Prompt Engineering

Natural Language & Visual Interfaces

📁 Repository Includes:
💻 Code samples for building full-stack AI apps

🔐 OpenAI API integration templates (Python/JS)

🧠 Prompt examples for ChatGPT and DALL·E

🎨 Use cases for image generation, chatbots, AI tools

✅ Mini-projects and guided application builds

🎯 Objective:
To gain hands-on experience in building AI-driven web and mobile applications using state-of-the-art models like GPT-4 and DALL·E, from concept to deployment.

